You are right, interval arithmetic is only briefly mentioned
at page xx and page 9 of the book.
    However, intervals instead of crisp values appear in Timoshenko beam 
problems or a plasticity model, for instance. The related mathematical 
problems are solved analytically or numerically using standard computer 
arithmetic.

